    "created_at": "2014-09-06T14:34:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-06T14:43:48Z",
    "body": "The Rust compiler uses a 6MiB stack and then increase than to 20MiB (!!!) when optimizations are disabled. The default stack size on Linux is 8MiB, so that's likely how much is available for the main thread. Rust tends to need a ridiculous amount of stack space, especially without optimizations.\n",
